That is, the present invention provides:
[1] An oral hygiene composition as defined in claim 1, comprising surface-treated microcrystalline cellulose having a coating of water-soluble polymer which is sodium carboxymethyl cellulose, contained at a weight ratio of microcrystalline cellulose to said sodium carboxymethyl cellulose in the range from 4:1 to 15:1.
[2] The oral hygiene composition according to aforementioned [1] which further contains a pharmacologically active ingredient;
[3] The oral hygiene composition according to aforementioned [2], wherein the pharmacologically active ingredient is one or more selected from the group consisting of an antimicrobial agent, an enzyme, a zinc compound, a vitamin and a derivative thereof, a fluoride compound, an amino acid, types of collagen, 6-aminocaproic acid, allantoin and derivatives thereof, dihydrocholesterol, glycyrrhizates, glycyrrhetinic acid, glycerophosphate, chlorophyll, potassium nitrate and sodium chloride;
[4] The oral hygiene composition according to aforementioned [2], wherein the pharmacologically active ingredient is one or more selected from the group consisting of cetylpyridinium chloride, triclosan, vitamin E and a derivative thereof, sodium fluoride, tranexamic acid and glycyrrhizate;
[5] The oral hygiene composition according to any one of aforementioned [1] to [4], which further contains an abrasive;
[6] The oral hygiene composition according to any one of aforementioned [1] to [5], which further contains a surfactant;
[7] The oral hygiene composition according to any one of aforementioned [1] to [6], wherein viscosity at 30°C of the composition is from 5 to 20 Pa·s; and
[8] The oral hygiene composition according to any one of aforementioned [1] to [7], which is used by ejecting onto a toothbrush from a pump container.
